@flexiarg eoi-engine/tension-cv-shape
@title EoI Tension Prompt — Non-Conventional CV Shape Honesty
@keywords eoi, cv, experience-floor, address-now, conventional-shape-fallacy, strawman-diagnostic
@audience operators authoring outward EoIs whose CV does not match the role's expected-shape (e.g. years-of-experience clauses calibrated to a particular career arc)
@tone diagnostic-prompt
@references [eoi-engine/eoi-outward-one-shot, writing-coherence/name-what-you-drop, structure/whose-question-is-this]


! conclusion:
  When an outward EoI is being authored for a role whose
  knowledge/experience clauses are calibrated to a particular
  career-arc shape (e.g. "7+ years in technical policy research /
  think-tank / applied research"), and the author's CV substantially
  exceeds the floor but in a non-conventional shape (e.g. distributed
  volunteer work, parallel research positions, dual roles), the EoI
  must name the unconventional shape rather than pretend conventionality.
  The pattern is similar to the foreclosure-honesty pattern: name what
  is true rather than what is expected.

  + context:
    Applies during `address-now` tagging of an EoI Tension on
    experience-floor / CV-shape clauses. The prompt asks: what
    relevant experience do you have, and what is the shape it takes
    that differs from the role's apparent expectation?

  + IF:
    The role's posting specifies an experience floor or a CV shape,
    AND the author's experience meets or exceeds the floor but in a
    shape the posting did not explicitly name.

  + HOWEVER:
    The underrepresented-groups paragraph in many postings does
    legitimate work — the EoI's response to a CV-shape clause should
    take that paragraph literally when present. Naming non-conventional
    shape is not the same as apology for it; the discipline is
    description, not deferral.

  + THEN:
    Author drafts a short CV-shape-honesty paragraph that names the
    substantive relevant experience (counted concretely where possible)
    in its actual shape, without forcing it into the conventional
    shape the posting implied.

  + BECAUSE:
    Per writing-coherence/name-what-you-drop and
    structure/whose-question-is-this: forcing one's CV into a shape
    the recipient expected is consultant-voice and risks under-counting
    relevant experience. Naming the actual shape is operator-voice and
    lets the recipient calibrate their reading accurately.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    Author drafts the CV-shape paragraph in their own register;
    eoi-engine assembly inserts it; reviewer checks that the relevant
    experience is named in its actual shape, with concrete duration
    or scope figures where available.

! source-note:
  Minted 2026-05-11 as part of the Arxana Essays annotation flow for
  the Anthropic Institute first-draft, alongside tension-foreclosure
  and tension-free-solo-rule. Surfaced from the strawman's diagnostic
  6 for that case ("7+ years experience clause reads as a floor for a
  particular shape of CV ... Joe has substantially more than 7 years
  but in a non-conventional shape").
